quran[44]{c,v,t}:
  38,52,"And with them shall be virgins of their own age, with modest retiring glances"
  38,53,This is what ye were promised at the day of reckoning
  38,54,"Yes! this is our provision: it shall never fail"
  38,55,Even so. But for the evil doers is a wretched home
  38,56,"Hell - wherein they shall be burned: how wretched a bed"
  38,57,Even so. Let them then taste it - boiling water and gore
  38,58,And other things of kindred sort
  38,59,"To their leaders it shall be said, \"This company shall be thrown in headlong with you. No greetings shall await them, for they shall be burned in the fire"
  38,60,"They shall say: \"But ye, too! there shall be no welcome for you. It was ye who prepared this for us, and wretched is the abode"
  38,61,"They will say: \"O our Lord! increase twofold in the fire, the punishment of him who hath brought this upon us"
  38,62,"And they will say: \"Why see we not the men whom we numbered among the wicked"
  38,63,Whom we used to treat with scorn? Have they escaped our eyes
  38,64,Verily this is truth - the wrangling together of the people of the fire
  38,65,"SAY: I am but a warner; and there is no God but God the One, the Almighty"
  38,66,"Lord of the Heavens and of the Earth, and of all that is between them, the Potent, the Forgiving"
  38,67,"SAY: this is a weighty message"
  38,68,From which ye turn aside
  38,69,Yet had I no knowledge of what passed among the celestial chiefs when they disputed
  38,70,"Verily, it hath been revealed to me only because I am a public preacher"
  38,71,"When thy Lord said to the angels, \"I am about to make man of clay"
  38,72,"And when I have formed him and breathed my spirit into him, then worshipping fall down before him"
  38,73,"And the angels prostrated themselves, all of them with one accord"
  38,74,"Save Eblis. He swelled with pride, and became an unbeliever"
  38,75,"O Eblis,\" said God, \"what hindereth thee from prostrating thyself before him whom my hands have made? Is it that thou are puffed up with pride? or art thou a being of lofty merit"
  38,76,"He said: \"I am more excellent than he; me hast thou created of fire: of clay hast thou created him"
  38,77,"He said: \"Begone then hence: thou art accursed"
  38,78,And lo! my ban shall be on thee till the day of the reckoning
  38,79,"He said: \"O my Lord! respite me till the day of Resurrection"
  38,80,"He said, \"One then of the respited shalt thou be"
  38,81,Till the day of the time appointed
  38,82,"He said: \"I swear by thy might then that all of them will I seduce"
  38,83,Save thy sincere servants among them
  38,84,"He said: \"It is truth, and the truth I speak"
  38,85,"From thee will I surely fill Hell, and with such of them as shall follow thee, one and all"
  38,86,"Say: I ask no wage of you for this, nor am I one who intermeddleth"
  38,87,Of a truth the Koran is no other than a warning to all creatures
  38,88,And after a time shall ye surely know its message
  39,1,"THE Book sent down from God, the Mighty, the Wise"
  39,2,"We have sent down the Book to thee with the truth: serve thou God then, and be sincere in thy worship"
  39,3,"Is not a sincere worship due to God? But they who take others beside him as lords saying, \"We serve them only that they may bring us near to God\" - God will judge between them and the faithful, concerning that wherein they are at variance. Verily God will not guide him who is a liar, an infidel"
  39,4,"Had God desired to have had a son, he had surely chosen what he pleased out of his own creation. But praise be to Him! He is God, the One, the Almighty"
  39,5,"For truth hath he created the Heavens and the Earth: It is of Him that the night returneth upon the day and that the day returneth upon the night: and He controlleth the sun and the moon so that each speedeth to an appointed goal. Is He not the Mighty, the Gracious"
  39,6,"He created you all of one man, from whom He afterwards formed his wife; and of cattle He hath sent down to you four pairs. In the wombs of your mothers did He create you by creation upon creation in triple darkness. It is He who is God your Lord: the kingdom is His: There is no God but He. How then are ye so turned aside from Him"
  39,7,"Suppose ye render him no thanks! yet forsooth is God rich without you: but He is not pleased with thanklessness in His servants: yet if ye be thankful He will be pleased with you. The soul burdened with its own works shall not be burdened with the burden of another: hereafter shall ye return to your Lord, and he will tell you of all your works, For he knoweth the very secrets of your breasts"